# Pre-Commit Checklist

Before committing, verify the following:

## Types
- [ ] Run `pnpm typegen` if any Sanity schema or GROQ query changed
- [ ] No TypeScript errors in changed files (check linter output)

## Schema sync
- [ ] If Sanity schemas changed, deploy to cloud: `pnpm dlx sanity@latest schema deploy`
- [ ] Schema barrel exports updated (`schemas/index.ts`, `schemas/modules/index.ts`, etc.)

## Pages and modules
- [ ] New modules registered in `ModuleRenderer.tsx` switch
- [ ] New modules added to `page.ts` modules array
- [ ] `loadQuery` used instead of direct `sanityClient.fetch` in pages
- [ ] Visual Editing props (`data-theme`, CSS variables) applied on themed sections

## Design system
- [ ] Brand colors used via tokens (not hardcoded hex)
- [ ] Layout uses `pp-container` / `pp-section` classes
- [ ] Typography uses `.eyebrow`, `.section-title`, `.section-subtitle` where appropriate

## Environment
- [ ] No secrets committed (`.env` is gitignored)
- [ ] `astro.config.mjs` uses `process.env`, not `import.meta.env`
- [ ] `sanity.config.ts` has dual-env fallback pattern

## Build
- [ ] `nvm use` to ensure correct Node version
- [ ] `pnpm build` succeeds without errors
